<TITLE> BNP challenges Qamrul on 'Zia spy' allegation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)--- BNP senior joint secretary general Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir has challenged state minister for law Qamrul Islam for his Friday's comment that Ziaur Rahman was a spy for Pakistan in 1971. "The comment is baseless. I am challenging the minister to prove it," Alamgir told a press briefing at BNP's Naya Paltan office on Saturday. He said that the comment is a 'violation of political etiquette'. He also wanted to know where Qamrul was during the liberation war. Alamgir counter-alleged that a group of Awami League leaders opposed independence and conspired to keep Pakistan intact. b
